    public class MainFrame
extends MapFrame
    Extends the functionality of the MapFrame class by adding the ability to manipulate existing data from within the SystemObjects database. This is accomplished primarily through the provision of a LineEditor that facilitates the editing of routes, route paths, and waypoints. This is the only MapFrame that allows the user to import & export data as well as exit the program.
    Author:
    Sean Harger

      • importRoutes

        private void importRoutes()
        Prompts the user to select a file from their file system and then creates a RouteImport to attempt to import route data from that file. Route data includes route numbers, paths, stops, and waypoints.

      • importServices

        private void importServices()
        Prompts the user to select a file from their file system and then creates a ServiceImport to attempt to import service data from that file. Service data includes periods, times, and all data including boardings, alightings, and load.

      • exportRoutes

        private void exportRoutes()
        Prompts the user to select a file from their file system and then creates a RouteExport to attempt to export modified route data from within MASS to that file. Route data includes route numbers, paths, stops, and waypoints.

      • openNewMap

        private void openNewMap()
        Creates a new secondary MapFrame. This is typically used to analyze data with different RoutePath and Service constraints than the current MapFrame.

      • openLineEditor

        private void openLineEditor()
        Creates a new LineEdit frame and opens it.

      • setUpGui

        private void setUpGui()
        Initializes the GUI elements of this MainFrame. Adds additional menu items not contained within a standard MapFrame and allows the closing of the MainFrame to terminate the program.

      • registerListeners

        private void registerListeners()
        Initializes the EventListeners for the GUI elements.
